      <div class="row spacer" id="what_is_BC">
          <h3 'Source Sans Pro'>What is Bulldog Clip?</h3>
          <p>Bulldog Clip was developed to take the pain out of tracking your costs, invoicing customers and reclaiming your expenses. This simple software removes the need for complicated spreadsheets, word processed invoices and addition done with a calculater. Let Bulldog Clip do all the hard work for you. Accessible online anywhere you have internet access. Available on mobile devices as well as desktops. You can process your spending wherever and whenever suits you. No more stacks of reciepts to process at the end of the month. You will be amazed at how much time it will save you.</p>
          <a class="top" href="#top">Back to top</a>
        </div>

      <hr>
      <div class="row spacer" id="who">
          <h3 'Source Sans Pro'>Who is Bulldog Clip for?</h3>
          <p>Although Bulldog Clip was designed for small businesses and sole-traders to capture there costs, it has also proved useful for individuals who just wish to track there household spending. If you currently battle every month to keep track of your costs using spreadsheets, create invoices using a word processor and add everything up with a calculator, Bulldog Clip will put a smile back on your face.</p>
          <a class="top" href="#top">Back to top</a>
        </div>

      <hr>
        <div class="row spacer" id="why_bulldog">
            <h3 'Source Sans Pro'>Why is it called Bulldog Clip</h3>
            <p>A bulldog clip is a simple and effective way of storing bills just like Bulldog Clip. When you get back from the shops you can keep all your reciepts neatly together in a bulldog clip until you are ready to process them onto the Bulldog Clip software.</p>
            <a class="top" href="#top">Back to top</a>
        </div>

      <hr>
        <div class="row spacer" id="bc_app">
            <h3 'Source Sans Pro'>Is there a Bulldog Clip app?</h3>
            <p>We don't have an app for Bulldog Clip. However the software has been designed to work just as well on a phone or tablet device as it does on your desktop computer.</p>
            <a class="top" href="#top">Back to top</a>
        </div>
      <hr>    
      <div class="row spacer" id="why_bills">
        <h3 'Source Sans Pro'>Why bills?</h3>
        <p>Most of what you are likely to record in Bulldog Clip are not strictly speaking 'bills'. They will often be receipts, till receipts, credit card transaction advice notes, or even invoices. Bill is a short and friendly name. That's why we use it. Not to be 'correct' but to be simple and effective, like a bulldog clip.</p>
        <a class="top" href="#top">Back to top</a>
      </div>

      <hr>
      <div class="row spacer" id="why_invoice">
          <h3 'Source Sans Pro'>Why invoices?</h3>
          <p>OK. Bill is short and simple but 'invoice' sounds technical and nine out of ten users will not need to create one - as an invoice. 
          It happens that the friend who first had a need for a better, simpler system, did have a need to invoice a client for expenses. (See the Story). When we were developing what became Bulldog Clip the name for the function just stuck. 
          Of course, you can choose what title you give the document and what appears on it. Invoice is a single, reasonably short word to use for what is actually a way to archive bills, to print organised lists of bills, to facilitate recovery of some of your costs and generally get enhanced value from using Bulldog Clip. 
          They are optional. You don't need to use them.</p>
          <a class="top" href="#top">Back to top</a>
        </div>

      <hr>
